  # Run `$searchMeta` Query Against Embedded Document Fields

  You can run [$searchMeta](pipe.$searchMeta) queries against the embedded
  document fields. In this section, you will connect to your Atlas
  cluster and run a sample query using the `$searchMeta` stage and
  facet on an embedded document field.

  ## Step 1: Connect to your cluster in .

  Open MongoDB Compass and connect to your cluster. For detailed
  instructions on connecting, see [Compass](atlas-connect-via-compass).

  ## Step 2: Use the  collection in the  database.

  On the Database screen, click the
  `local_school_district` database, and then click the `schools`
  collection.

  ## Step 3: Run the following  queries against the  collection.

  This query finds the high schools and requests a count of the number
  of schools that offer classes in each grade.

  | Pipeline Stage | Query                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
  | -------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
  | $searchMeta    | \{ "index": "embedded-embedded-documents-tutorial", "facet": \{ "operator": \{ "text":\{ "path": "name", "query": "High" } }, "facets": \{ "gradeFacet": \{ "type": "string", "path": "teachers.classes.grade" } } } }MongoDB Compass displays the following in the results:count: Object lowerBound: 3 facet: Object gradeFacet: Object buckets: Array (4) 0: Object \_id: "12th" count: 3 1: Object \_id: "9th" count : 3 2: Object \_id: "10th" count: 2 3: Object \_id: "11th" count: 1The results show that 3 schools offer classes for 12th and 9th grades, 2 schools offer classes for 10th grade, and 1 school offers classes for 11th grade. When you facet by a field inside an embedded document, the query returns count for the top-level parent document, which is the teachers field for this query. |
